HOUSE BILL 1568
L6 6lr3546
By: Delegate Ross
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Judiciary
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Local Government – Animal Control – Dogs At Large
3 (Dog Leash Laws)
4 FOR the purpose of requiring each county and municipality to adopt local laws or
5 regulations prohibiting a dog from being at large; and generally relating to local laws
6 regulating animal control.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Local Government
9 Section 1–1321
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2013 Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Local Government
15 1–1321.
16 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES TO ALL COUNTIES AND MUNICIPALITIES.
17 (B) EACH COUNTY AND MUNICIPALITY SHALL ADOPT A LOCAL LAW:
18 (1) PROHIBITING THE OWNER OF A DOG FROM ALLOWING A DOG TO
19 BE AT LARGE;
20 (2) ESTABLISHING PROCEDURES FOR THE IMPOUNDMENT OF A DOG
21 FOUND AT LARGE BY AN ANIMAL CONTROL UNIT OR OTHER ENFORCEMENT ENTITY;
22 AND
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1568*

2 HOUSE BILL 1568
1 (3) ESTABLISHING PENALTIES FOR A VIOLATION, INCLUDING CIVIL
2 AND CRIMINAL PENALTIES.
3 (C) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO PREEMPT A LOCAL
4 GOVERNMENT FROM ENACTING AND ENFORCING MORE STRINGENT MEASURES
5 THAN THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That it is the intent of the General
7 Assembly that this Act be applied and interpreted to recognize the definition of the term
8 “running at large” as used by the Appellate Court of Maryland in Blitzer v. Breski, 259 Md.
9 App. 257 (2023).
10 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 October 1, 2026.

